        <p><strong>Robert, age 64 — founder of SnapProtein.</strong> I used to think hitting my daily protein number was the whole job. Then I looked at when I was actually eating it. Most of my protein was at dinner. Which meant most of my day I was losing ground, not gaining it. Pacing fixed that.</p>
