    <!-- QUICK ANSWER -->
    <div class="quick-answer">
      <h3>Quick Answer</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Muscle protein synthesis is triggered per meal — your daily total doesn't override per-meal dosing.</li>
        <li>Each meal needs at least 30g of protein to flip the anabolic switch after 40.</li>
        <li>Meals below 30g don't contribute to muscle building — regardless of what you eat at dinner.</li>
        <li>Even protein distribution across 3–4 meals produces 25% more muscle protein synthesis than the same total eaten unevenly.</li>
        <li>The goal: 4 anabolic windows per day, spaced 4–5 hours apart, each clearing 30–40g.</li>
      </ul>
